🚀 Step 1: Download Jenkins (Official WAR)
wget https://get.jenkins.io/war-stable/latest/jenkins.war
▶️ Step 2: Run Jenkins
java -jar jenkins.war

You’ll see logs like:

Jenkins is fully up and running
🌐 Step 3: Access Jenkins

Open browser:

http://<your-server-ip>:8080
🔐 Step 4: Get Initial Password

In terminal logs OR run:

cat ~/.jenkins/secrets/initialAdminPassword
🔍 Step 1: Confirm Jenkins is Listening on Port 8080

Run:

ss -tulnp | grep 8080

👉 Expected output:

LISTEN 0 50 0.0.0.0:8080
❗ If you see:
127.0.0.1:8080

➡ Jenkins is only accessible locally, not from browser outside

🔧 Step 2: Fix Binding (if needed)

Run Jenkins like this:

java -jar jenkins.war --httpListenAddress=0.0.0.0

This makes it accessible externally.

🌐 Step 3: Use Correct URL
If on same machine:
http://localhost:8080
If on VM / server:
http://<your-server-ip>:8080

Get IP:

ip a

Look for something like:

inet 192.168.x.x
🔥 Step 4: Check Firewall (VERY COMMON ISSUE)
Ubuntu firewall:
sudo ufw status

If active, allow port:

sudo ufw allow 8080
☁️ Step 5: If on Cloud (AWS / Azure / GCP)

You MUST open port 8080 in:

Security Group / Firewall rules

Allow:

Port: 8080
